      • setMaxTransactionFee

        public final T setMaxTransactionFee(Hbar fee)
        Sets the maximum fee that the client is willing to pay to execute this transaction, which is split between the network and the node.

        The actual fee assessed may be less than this, in which case you will only be charged that amount. An error is thrown if the assessed fee is greater than this.

        The calculation of the fee depends on the type of the transaction and its parameters, as well as the current fee schedule of the network.

        Defaults to the value of Client.setMaxTransactionFee(long).

      • setMaxTransactionFee

        public final T setMaxTransactionFee(long fee)
        Sets the maximum fee, in tinybar, that the client is willing to pay to execute this transaction, which is split between the network and the node.

        The actual fee assessed may be less than this, in which case you will only be charged that amount. An error is thrown if the assessed fee is greater than this.

        The calculation of the fee depends on the type of the transaction and its parameters, as well as the current fee schedule of the network.

        Defaults to the value of Client.setMaxTransactionFee(long).

      • setTransactionValidDuration

        public final T setTransactionValidDuration(Duration validDuration)
        Sets the the duration that this transaction is valid for. The transaction must reach consensus before this elapses.

        The duration will be capped at 2 minutes as that is the maximum validDuration for the network.

      • setTransactionMemo

      • build

        public final Transaction build(@Nullable
                               Client client)
                        throws LocalValidationException
        Construct the final, immutable transaction.

        If client is not null, then some defaults are added if they are not otherwise set:

        • setNodeAccountId(AccountId), if not manually set, is set with a random node chosen from the set that Client was constructed with
        • setMaxTransactionFee(Hbar), if not manually set, is set with the value of Client.getMaxTransactionFee()
        • setTransactionId(TransactionId) is set by calling TransactionId.TransactionId(AccountId) with the operator account if perviously set by Client.setOperator(AccountId, PrivateKey).
        • Transaction.sign(PrivateKey) is called with the operator private key if also previously set by Client.setOperator(AccountId, PrivateKey) (but only if setTransactionId(TransactionId) was not called with a different account ID in the transaction ID).
        The last two items imply that the operator account set with Client.setOperator(AccountId, PrivateKey) will be paying the fee for this transaction if not otherwise specified.
        Parameters:
        client - the client to retrieve defaults from.
        Returns:
        the built Transaction, signed by the operator key in the client if applicable.
        Throws:
        LocalValidationException - if the transaction fails local sanity checks.
